âœª Factors to Consider:
1ï¸âƒ£  When designing a transmission medium, important factors to consider include greater bandwidth, noise, and transmission impairment.Bandwidth refers to the capacity of the medium to carry data. Noise can interfere with the signal, reducing the quality of communication.ğŸ› ï¸
